video.title: Good Morning Call
video.synopsis: A high school girl finally gets her own apartment, but she has to share it with the most popular boy in school. No one can know they're living together.

episodes.synopsis: Nao moves into her own apartment, but a male classmate shows up and says he's the real tenant. They find a solution but it won't be easy to pull off.
episodes.title: Alone at Last

episodes.synopsis: Nao is still reeling from the morning's events but Uehara doesn't remember a thing. Marina suspects something is up and starts asking questions.
episodes.title: A Kiss to Remember

episodes.synopsis: Nao tends to Uehara, who is hospitalized from overworking. A mysterious woman appears. Rumors buzz at school that Uehara and Nao are an item.
episodes.title: Rumor Has It

episodes.synopsis: With Christmas Eve fast approaching, an unfortunate encounter with a delivery boy leads Nao to a new job, where she meets Abe, the "confession king."
episodes.title: Christmas is Coming

episodes.synopsis: A confession to Abe confuses Nao's relationship with Uehara further. Later, she hears that he'll be spending New Year's with his coworker, Nanako.
episodes.title: Party of One

episodes.synopsis: At Marina's suggestion, Nao and Uehara eat a lunch bento together in public. It's fun, but she wonders if he's thinking of Yuri when they're together.
episodes.title: Faking Up is Hard to Do

episodes.synopsis: Yuri announces she's getting divorced and asks to stay at the apartment. Uehara goes home to his brother, leaving Yuri and Nao to live alone together.
episodes.title: Baby, It's Cold Outside

episodes.synopsis: Uehara's older brother, Takuya, tries to explain himself, but Yuri isn't having it and throws away her wedding ring. Nao works to help them reconcile.
episodes.title: He's Not Sexy, He's My Brother

episodes.synopsis: Nao overhears Uehara talking about his feelings for her. Too flummoxed to respond, she avoids him. Marina suggests a Valentine's Day date.
episodes.title: A Valentine Surprise

episodes.synopsis: Nao finds out Yuri stayed overnight and announces she'll be moving out. Daichi calls Uehara to a one-on-one meeting on the school rooftop.
episodes.title: A Change of Scenery

episodes.synopsis: The parents find out the truth and Uehara leaves to live at home. When her father cancels the contract, Nao runs away and Uehara goes to face him.
episodes.title: Father Knows Best

episodes.synopsis: In an effort to rebuff Yukari's overtures, Icchan claims Nao is his girlfriend. Uehara overhears, but his lack of a reaction worries Nao.
episodes.title: Tagging Along

episodes.synopsis: Transfer student Nozomi Kitaura confronts Nao on the rooftop and shares her feelings about Uehara. Worried, Nao plans a special date with him.
episodes.title: The Getaway (Part 1)

episodes.synopsis: Uehara’s presence alone puts Nao on cloud nine, but Issei throws her looks with mixed feelings. By chance, Nao is paired with Issei for a dare night.
episodes.title: The Getaway (Part 2)

episodes.synopsis: After the trip, Nao is hospitalized for food poisoning and meets a kind college student. She learns that Uehara has been having a cute girl over.
episodes.title: Surprise!

episodes.synopsis: Issei has moved into the apartment after a family fight. Marina has her eye on a visiting college student, whom Nao recognizes from the hospital.
episodes.title: Two is Company...

episodes.synopsis: Nao mistakenly assumes Uehara will propose to her, and engagement rumors spread throughout the school. After he denies it to her face, she collapses.
episodes.title: A Modest Proposal

episodes.synopsis: Nao and Uehara head off to college, but Uehara's popularity worries Nao, and their new acquaintance Natsume seems to want to separate them.
episodes.title: Campus Life Is Full of Temptation

episodes.synopsis: A kiss incident with Natsume causes misunderstandings between Uehara and Nao. He takes a job in a lab while she scopes out clubs at college.
episodes.title: Mission: Get More Girly!!

episodes.synopsis: Nao learns that Uehara is on first name terms with Saeko in his lab. She confides her fears to Natsume during a trip to a petting zoo with his sister.
episodes.title: Love or Friendship?

episodes.synopsis: With Uehara's birthday approaching, Nao takes a job at the store where Natsume works. A customer's request makes them both think about what they want.
episodes.title: First Love Never Lasts?

episodes.synopsis: Natsume and Nao take lead roles in Abecchi's play, but the script's kiss scenes annoy Uehara. Meanwhile, Micchan and Marina are on the rocks.
episodes.title: Playing a Tragic Heroine's Fun!

episodes.synopsis: Nao plans a surprise party for Uehara's birthday, but unbeknownst to her, he quickly finds out about it. Natsume gives Nao some advice.
episodes.title: His Birthday Surprise

episodes.synopsis: Uehara suspects Natsume has feelings for Nao. Natsume confides in Saeko, and Nanase and Nao discuss love while working on a project.
episodes.title: For Friendship.

episodes.synopsis: Nao doesn't tell Uehara that Natsume kissed her, but he figures it out. Nao, Natsume and the group go camping while Uehara and Saeko attend a lecture.
episodes.title: Careful When Camping at Night

episodes.synopsis: Nao stresses out after Uehara tells her he wants some space. Worrying about her, Natsume punches Uehara, then tells Nao how he feels.
episodes.title: Can You Fall Out of Love?

episodes.synopsis: Uehara and Nao have broken up, and Nao is trying to reinvent herself. She hopes they'll get back together, but Saeko's feelings haven't changed.
episodes.title: Give Me a Good Morning Call Tomorrow
